### Key decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| One `it()` per AC | Direct traceability — a failing test name immediately identifies which criterion broke |
| AC6 uses `credit_card` | Fee is 0, so `refundAmount === 10000` — clean assertion with no arithmetic offset |
| AC5 uses `10001` not `99999` | Smallest integer violation; tests the guard precisely, not incidentally |
| Both `fee` and `refundAmount` asserted in AC1/AC2 | The criterion is about fee *deduction*, so both sides of the math must be verified |

